<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 96-08-01 - Small Aero Roof Mounted Clearance and Marker Lamps</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi960801" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>96-08-01</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>January, 1996</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ELECTRICAL</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Small Aero Roof Mounted Clearance and Marker Lamps</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9400</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Under some operating conditions, a vacuum may be created inside the cab of 9200, 9300 and 9400 Pro
                    Sleeper Models. Water may be drawn inside the clearance and marker lamps (P/N 2031355C91), between
                    the lens and lamp base.
                </para>
                <para>On vehicles built after July 17, 1995, an O-ring was added between the lens and lamp base. Adding
                    the O-ring greatly reduced the tendency of the lamp to leak, but under all conditions may not be
                    100% effective.
                </para>
                <para>Vehicles built after January 2,1996. will have a flat gasket installed between the lens and base
                    of lamp (P/N 2031355C91).
                </para>
                <para>This letter contains parts and service information to install a gasket in roof mounted clearance
                    and marker lamps (P/N 2031355C91) on 9200, 9300 and 9400 Pro Sleeper Models.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <table id="t9608011" frame="all">
                <title>Parts Information</title>
